1
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,680
(Episode 6)

2
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:41,760
Yan, the flowers you requested are ready.

3
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:45,720
Let's go.

4
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:45,760
Stay there.

5
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,480
Come over.

6
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,240
Be quick if you're giving your lecture.

7
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:57,400
I'm meeting friends.

8
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,960
You've told me that

9
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,800
being late is a great insult to others.

10
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,360
Look at you. Sleep in daytime

11
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,800
and go out at night.

12
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,760
What are you up to every day?

13
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,040
Take it easy.

14
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,640
I don't traffic humans.

15
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:11,120
I don't kill or commit arson.

16
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,800
I'm not involved in sex or drug deals.

17
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,520
I'm just going out with friends to enjoy

18
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,200
the nightlife in my hometown.

19
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,200
How long do you plan to live like this?

20
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,640
Listen,...

21
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,320
Shenghai Group is hiring soon.

22
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,080
Get well prepared for this.

23
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,400
Dad,

24
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:29,400
just because you couldn't defeat
Zhou Yanzhao to become the chairman,

25
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,760
now you're forcing me to do this.

26
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,400
I refuse to be his training partner.

27
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:35,000
Please spare me.

28
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:35,960
Listen,

29
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,600
I'm not discussing with you.

30
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,920
I'm informing you.

31
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,960
You must get into Shenghai Group.

32
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,400
Why must I work in Shenghai?

33
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,920
Because you're Jiang Qingcheng's son,

34
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:48,000
you can't lose to Zhou Binli's son.

35
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,640
I'd rather not be your son

36
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,720
than to work at Shenghai.

37
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,760
I'll cut all your credit cards...

38
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,000
You!

39
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,120
unless you get a job in Shenghai.

40
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,160
Are you really my dad?

41
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:04,560
Ze,...

42
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,080
I've got to have a perfect plan

43
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,400
for your life

44
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,440
because I'm your dad.

45
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,240
Remember,...

46
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,600
you've been called
the second generation of the rich.

47
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:17,440
The term weighs more than you've imagined.

48
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,440
Since you were born,

49
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:20,920
you've been bearing

50
00:04:20,960 --> 00:04:23,720
a greater burden than
your previous generation.

51
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:26,320
You don't just inherit wealth.

52
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:28,520
You have more pressure and challenges.

53
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:31,120
The competition is crueler.

54
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,760
I'm not interested
in anything you've just said.

55
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,800
I can't help you
even if I work in Shenghai.

56
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:38,000
This is only the first step.

57
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:41,520
I know the details of Zhou Binli's will.

58
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,000
The next step is

59
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:46,040
to have you marry Zhou Xiaomeng.

60
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,640
I want to live my life in my own way.

61
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,000
When you're older,

62
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:58,040
you'll know how childish your words are.

63
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:04,800
Yan,...

64
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,720
I'll go back to my room first.

65
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:16,680
Yan,...

66
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,560
Please don't, and listen to me.

67
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,200
Yan, don't act like this.
Where are you taking me?

68
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:23,040
-Yan, where are you going?
-Back off.

69
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,640
Yan!

70
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:32,960
Get off.

71
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:37,160
You've brought me to Mr. Zhou's cemetery.

72
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,280
Let's go.

73
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,160
Yan!

74
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,560
Zhou Xiaomeng, look carefully.

75
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,640
My dad has just passed away,...

76
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,880
but you're dressed in red on TV
for the whole world to see.

77
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,720
Listen to me, Yan.

78
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:57,080
It was just for work,

79
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,360
-so--
-Don't explain to me.

80
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,560
Explain to my dad.

81
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,760
My dad was good to you and your mom.

82
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,400
He even left you Shenghai's shares.

83
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,320
Even if you don't appreciate,

84
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:08,360
can't you just pretend
to show him some respect?

85
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:09,840
Uncle Zhou,...

86
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,120
I'm sorry.

87
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,440
I'm sorry.

88
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:17,960
Do you like me?

89
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:22,680
Yes.

90
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,360
If you like me,...

91
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,360
you should respect me.

92
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:29,000
You shouldn't have been dressed
in bright red and smile on TV.

93
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,000
I'm sorry, Yan.

94
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:33,680
I'm sorry.

95
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:34,800
You're sorry?

96
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:37,560
Sorry doesn't mean anything.

97
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:41,520
Dad, rest assured.

98
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,600
Shenghai Group is your lifetime's work.

99
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:48,120
I won't let it fall apart.

100
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:53,280
For those who've betrayed you,...

101
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,800
I'll have them pay gravely.

102
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:15,880
Trained before?

103
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,800
No formal training. I box for fun.

104
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,120
Practice with me.

105
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,800
You're too tired, Yan.

106
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,800
Take a break.

107
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:15,800
The cemetery.

108
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:19,960
She's in the cemetery.

109
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,360
Do you still remember this, Yan?

110
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:31,200
You gave this to me.

111
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,680
We were in the sports center.

112
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,920
You said I looked like goofy Garfield.

113
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,200
-Are you hurt?
-I'm fine.

114
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,680
How did you get hurt? Allow me.

115
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:45,720
I'm okay.

116
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,400
It may hurt a little bit.

117
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,800
Bear it.

118
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,080
I feel nothing.

119
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:57,640
You're pretending.

120
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,200
Does it hurt now?

121
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,720
She's killing me. Help!

122
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,480
She's trying to kill her own husband!

123
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,160
Stop your nonsense.

124
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,960
I've got a wound.

125
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,240
Why are you using a facial mask?

126
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,760
I don't have any bandages,

127
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,560
so I'm using this instead.

128
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,720
You do look like this goofy Garfield.

129
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,840
I've got bandages.

130
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:29,920
Let me.

131
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,080
We were so happy at that time.

132
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:44,880
Garfield, I envy you to be so carefree.

133
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,120
If only in life,...

134
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:48,640
when times are tough,...

135
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:51,320
I could just goof around.

136
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,160
Hang in there,...

137
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,920
Zhou Xiaomeng. You're the toughest!

138
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,280
Big Eyes.

139
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,040
Yan asks you to stay home today

140
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,080
as you have no classes.

141
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,000
Guang,...

142
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:33,000
I just wanted to go to the sports store

143
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,640
to buy Yan a pair of boxing gloves.

144
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:37,840
Alright.

145
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,840
Don't put me in a difficult position.

146
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,440
Big Eyes, let's go.

147
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:53,320
Miss, our boxing gloves are all here.

148
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,800
This pair is imported from the U.S.

149
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,120
It's a bit more expensive

150
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,480
but the quality is really good.

151
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,120
Give me a pair of these red gloves.

152
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,120
Sure.

153
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,440
The black ones too.

154
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,640
Yes, Miss.

155
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,800
Is your boyfriend a boxer?

156
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,640
He...

157
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,400
Yes.

158
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,400
A boxer for a boyfriend
surely makes you feel safe.

159
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,640
Please check out at the counter.

160
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,640
Why have they parked so close?

161
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,080
Hello, A Qi.

162
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,760
Where are you, Xiaomeng?

163
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,800
Listen. The director
and the crew are all here.

164
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,520
Don't be late.

165
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,640
I'm nearby.

166
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:40,760
I'll be there in a minute.

167
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,080
But...

168
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,560
I bumped into someone's car.

169
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:46,640
What should I do?

170
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,240
Is it serious?

171
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:52,880
It's probably okay.

172
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,320
You should just apologize
and pay for the damages.

173
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:58,760
Listen, the director is quick-tempered.

174
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,200
Make sure you come on time.

175
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:02,160
He just scolded his assistant severely.

176
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,800
Alright. I've got it.

177
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:04,840
I'll come soon.

178
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:05,920
Calm him down first.

179
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:06,920
That's it for now. Bye!

180
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,160
See you tonight

181
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:41,600
-in our usual place.
-Sure.

182
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:42,800
-Bye-bye.
-Bye-bye...

183
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:01,720
How can I be so unlucky?

184
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,720
Zhou Xiaomeng.

185
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,120
Do you like it?

186
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,120
Yes.

187
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:22,600
Shall I give it to you?

188
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:23,440
Yes.

189
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:26,680
Let's call it "Weekend," shall we?

190
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,560
Okay.

191
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,040
Why are Xiaomeng's eyes so red?

192
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:32,560
What's up?

193
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:33,880
Director,

194
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,520
she worked long hours yesterday.

195
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:37,040
She probably hasn't got enough rest.

196
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,240
We've bought some eye drop for her.

197
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:40,160
She's used it.

198
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,200
Her eyes will be fine soon.

199
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:44,960
How about we take the wide shot first.

200
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,880
Cameraman,...

201
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,600
we'll take the wide shot first.

202
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:51,480
Wide shot first. Get ready.

203
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,360
It's okay now.

204
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,400
Get ready. Follow the camera.

205
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,240
Surrounding us,...

206
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,800
there's this group of kids.

207
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,400
They can see...

208
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,760
but they don't look
at anything around them.

209
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:09,040
They can hear...

210
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,240
but they don't listen to anything.

211
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:14,080
They can make sounds...

212
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,760
but they don't know

213
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:18,080
how to communicate with this world.

214
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:23,360
They're the kids of the stars.

215
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,440
Cut! Cut! Cut!

216
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,440
Xiaomeng, what's the matter with you?

217
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,440
I'm really sorry, director.

218
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:34,800
I just had a stumble.

219
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:36,160
Can we have another take?

220
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,560
Let's take

221
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,080
the kid's close-up first.

222
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,600
Xiaomeng, go take a break.

223
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:49,400
Get ready.

224
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:52,400
Three, two, one. Action!

225
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:58,960
Anything wrong?

226
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:00,880
No.

227
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,720
The director must have
a bad impression of me.

228
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,440
I can feel it.

229
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:08,480
I think it doesn't matter.

230
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:10,080
You have good work ethic.

231
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:11,600
Everyone knows that.

232
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:13,880
You didn't do it on purpose anyway.

233
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:15,520
Don't worry.

234
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:24,000
Whose call are you waiting for?

235
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:27,480
Didn't I tell you I bumped into a car?

236
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,400
I left my phone number for the car owner.

237
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:31,080
My phone is on mute.

238
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:33,280
I'm afraid
I might miss that person's call.

239
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:39,720
This one.

240
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,800
I think it's from the car owner.

241
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:44,840
He's not looking this way right now.

242
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,280
Go out and answer it.

243
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:48,920
If he asks,
I'll say you're in the washroom.

244
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,520
-Thanks!
-Hurry up. Go.

245
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:03,760
Hello? Is this Zhou Xiaomeng?

246
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:05,440
Yes.

247
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:08,920
Are you the owner of the car
that I bumped into today?

248
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,680
Yes, I am.

249
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,040
I'm really sorry.

250
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,400
I wasn't paying attention.

251
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:15,640
But please be assured

252
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,720
I'll take responsibility.

253
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:18,480
I'll pay the compensation in full.

254
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:21,200
I don't care about the money.

255
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:24,480
But you crushed my car's bumper
and ran away.

256
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,840
This is a hit-and-run accident.

257
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:29,680
I...I didn't run away.

258
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,680
I left you a note.

259
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:32,880
A note?

260
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,560
The wind must have blown it away.

261
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:36,040
I haven't seen any note.

262
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,280
Impossible.

263
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:39,720
How can you tell such a blatant lie?

264
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:42,920
How could you get
my number without my note?

265
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,440
I'll explain it when I see you.

266
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:46,760
I'm hungry now.

267
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,000
Today at noon.

268
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:50,480
Let's meet up at New Betsy's Restaurant.

269
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,240
Noon?

270
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,560
I'm afraid I can't make it.

271
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:55,520
If you don't come,

272
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:57,120
I'll see this as hit-and-run.

273
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,240
I--

274
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,240
He's such a weirdo.

275
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:36,480
Chairman Zhou.

276
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,280
Ladies and gentlemen,

277
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:45,560
this is Mr. Zhou Yanzhao,
chairman of Shenghai Group.

278
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:51,400
Chairman Zhou will personally host
this part of the interview.

279
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:08,840
Please sit down.

280
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,200
Qingyan,...

281
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,040
shouldn't there be six candidates?

282
00:21:20,120 --> 00:21:21,360
